  <div class="box en">💡 <strong>Takeaway:</strong> U.S. spot bitcoin ETFs drew net inflows on July 2 (+$216M) and July 6 (+$294.8M), halting an eight-week outflow run; the July 6 haul was mostly IBIT ($187M) and FBTC ($62M). It contrasts with June's $4.1B drain, and the weekly net outflow narrowed from ~$2B to ~$700M. Yet falling open interest and weak spot demand left price stuck near $63K. ETF inflows are a floor against declines, not a guarantee of upside. Watch the persistence of inflows, issuer concentration, and OI alignment. Sources: CoinDesk, The Block, Farside, CoinGlass.</div>
